Natural.definition: based on an inherent sense of right and wrong [ justice] see also natural law

1.definition: based on an inherent sense of right and wrong [ justice] see also,

2 a.definition: existing as part of or determined by nature [the condition of the land]

sub_terms.b: being in accordance with or arising from nature esp. as distinguished from operation of law see alsocompare
sub_terms.c: arising from the usual course of events [a result of the accident]

sub_terms.b: being a relation by consanguinity as distinguished from adoption [ parents]
